        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">Along with this project, you have been attributed an Ubuntu server, living in a datacenter far far away. Like level 2 of the application process, you will connect using <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>ssh</code>. But contrary to level 2, you will not connect using a password but an RSA key. We&rsquo;ve configured your server with the public key you created in the first task of <a href="https://intranet.hbtn.io/rltoken/LZ_8pMANOAmpn5-tiwqiJQ" style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(224, 0, 60); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" title="a previous project">a previous project</a> shared in your <a href="https://intranet.hbtn.io/rltoken/l4Ao4ESbI_hMB6s4mjBKRw" style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(224, 0, 60); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" title="intranet profile">intranet profile</a>.</p>
